Dead, Missing From March 11 Quake in Japan Falls Below 20,000

-- B y   S t u a r t   B i g g s
-- 
2011-09-06T10:08:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/dead-missing-from-march-11-quake-in-japan-falls-below-20-000.html
The number of dead and missing
following the magnitude-9 earthquake and tsunami that struck
Japan on March 11 fell to 19,996, according to the  National
Police Agency  in Tokyo.  The number of confirmed dead was 15,769, with 4,227 people
missing, the agency said in a statement today.  Previous statements had the dead and missing at more than
20,000 people.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stuart Biggs in Tokyo at 
 sbiggs3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter Langan at 
 plangan@bloomberg.net  